# Luau Conventions

- Always use `.luau` extension, never `.lua`
- Use `local` for all variables ‚Äî no globals
- Prefer `type` annotations on function parameters and return types
- Use `export type` for types shared across modules
- Require via aliases (`@packages`, `@utils`, `@constants`, `@global`, etc.) defined in `.luaurc`
- Never use `wait()` ‚Äî use `task.wait()`, `task.spawn()`, `task.defer()`
- Use `table.freeze` / `objects.deepFreeze` for immutable data structures

## Module Pattern

```luau
-- Public API at end of file
local function doThing()
end

return {
    doThing = doThing,
}
```

## Naming

- `camelCase` for variables, functions, fields
- `PascalCase` for types, classes, components
- `UPPER_SNAKE` for true constants only
- File names: `camelCase.luau` for modules, `name.client.luau` / `name.server.luau` for scripts
